values:
so i went home for easter weekend and i'm glad that i did so...

this morning for easter my mommy had me go on an easter egg hunt when i woke up which i'm not going to lie was a lot of fun...then we also baked cookies today which i haven't done in forever so i'm glad that i got to do so....

some other things happened but i really dont' want to get into detail about them because they really weren't for the better...but it's ok because i wasn't going ot let it ruin my extremely short weekend home....

so i realized how much in some ways that i missed home and i'm glad that i came home...and in some perspectives i dont' want to leave right now(and you know who you are who knows exactly what this is about and why)...but i just have to keep telling my self that i will be back in a short time(4 weeks) and all will be well..and i just have to remember to enjoy my last four weeks of my freshmen year...because i will never be able to go back!

i'm definitely tired right now...but i can't sleep...it could possibly be because i took about a three hour nap today..i was completely a waste of space today...and that's all i have been today is a waste of space and life...i hope that everyone else has had a great day...i have been cleaning and everything else...it's been great fun...

ok...so i'm sitting down in chandler right now wide awake and talking to people...i hate this when i can't sleep...i don't have class until 4:49 tomorrow so i'm not even going to worry about it...i don't exactly know what else i'm doing right now...i'm just hanging out and hwat not...and so much more...

it's my second semester of my freshman year and it's off to a new start which should be quite interesting...i hope that everything goes well and what not...i'm excited...everything is going well so far!

and thanks to my freakin amazing friend dan...my myspace profile song is the best!

so my absolutely A-mAzing friend Dan created my journal for me which i greatly appreciate...it's not just another thing for me to handle...but it's ok..it will be fun in the long run...

it's friday night...we are goin out but we just aren't sure what's going on...lol! this should be quite interesting
